&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re delivering work that comes back with a few sharpening comments, not heavy rewrites. You&#39;re asking the right questions before you start, not after. You&#39;re someone your manager and clients can rely on — and you&#39;re already noticing how the work could be done better and saying so.&lt;/p&gt;
